<paragraph blockId="27.[818,1442,869,977]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
This species is known from one specimen from mixed hardwood cloud forest at 
<quantity box="[961,1040,928,948]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.114" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="1114.0">1,114 m</quantity>
elevation. The specimen is from a Winkler sample of forest floor litter and rotten wood.
</paragraph>
